content.text: TensorFlow.js Tutorial
What is TensorFlow.js?
Tensorflow is popular JavaScript library for Machine Learning .
content.html: Tensorflow is popular JavaScript library for Machine Learning.

content.text: Tensorflow lets us train and deploy machine learning in the Browser .
content.html: Tensorflow lets us train and deploy machine learning in the Browser.

content.text: Tensorflow lets us add machine learning functions to any Web Application .
content.html: Tensorflow lets us add machine learning functions to any Web Application.

content.text: Using TensorFlow
To use TensorFlow.js, add the following script tag to your HTML file(s):
content.html: To use TensorFlow.js, add the following script tag to your HTML file(s):

content.code_html: <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs@3.6.0/dist/tf.min.js"></script>

content.text: If you always want to use the latest version, drop the version number:
content.html: If you always want to use the latest version, drop the version number:

content.code_html: <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@tensorflow/tfjs"></script>

content.text: TensorFlow was developed by the Google Brain Team for internal Google use, but was released as open software in 2015.
content.html: TensorFlow was developed by the Google Brain Team for internal Google use, but was released as open software in 2015.

content.text: In January 2019, Google developers released TensorFlow.js, the JavaScript Implementation of TensorFlow.
content.html: In January 2019, Google developers released TensorFlow.js, the JavaScript Implementation of TensorFlow.

content.text: Tensorflow.js was designed to provide the same features as the original TensorFlow library written in Python.
content.html: Tensorflow.js was designed to provide the same features as the original TensorFlow library written in Python.

content.text: Tensors
TensorFlow.js is a JavaScript library to define and operate on Tensors .
content.html: TensorFlow.js is a JavaScript library to define and operate on Tensors.

content.text: The main data type in TensorFlow.js is the Tensor .
content.html: The main data type in TensorFlow.js is the Tensor.

content.text: A Tensor is much the same as a multidimensional array.
content.html: A Tensor is much the same as a multidimensional array.

content.text: A Tensor contains values in one or more dimensions:
content.html: A Tensor contains values in one or more dimensions:

content.text: A Tensor has the following main properties:
content.html: A Tensor has the following main properties:

content.text: Sometimes in machine learning, the term " dimension " is used interchangeably with " rank .
content.html: Sometimes in machine learning, the term "dimension" is used interchangeably with "rank.

content.text: [10, 5] is a 2-dimensional tensor or a 2-rank tensor.
content.html: [10, 5] is a 2-dimensional tensor or a 2-rank tensor.

content.text: In addition the term "dimensionality" can refer to the size of a one dimension.
content.html: In addition the term "dimensionality" can refer to the size of a one dimension.

content.text: Example: In the 2-dimensional tensor [10, 5], the dimensionality of the first dimension is 10.
content.html: Example: In the 2-dimensional tensor [10, 5], the dimensionality of the first dimension is 10.

content.text: Creating a Tensor
The main data type in TensorFlow is the Tensor .
content.html: The main data type in TensorFlow is the Tensor.

content.text: A Tensor is created from any N-dimensional array with the tf.tensor() method:
content.html: A Tensor is created from any N-dimensional array with the tf.tensor() method:

content.code_html:
const myArr = [[1, 2, 3, 4]];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr);

content.text: Tensor Shape
A Tensor can also be created from an array and a shape parameter:
content.html: A Tensor can also be created from an array and a shape parameter:

content.code_html:
const myArr = [1, 2, 3, 4]:
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape);

content.text: Retrieve Tensor Values
You can get the data behind a tensor using tensor.data() :
content.html: You can get the data behind a tensor using tensor.data():

content.code_html:
const myArr = [[1, 2], [3, 4]];
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape);
tensorA.data().then(data => display(data));

function display(data) {
  document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = data;
}

content.text: You can get the array behind a tensor using tensor.array() :
content.html: You can get the array behind a tensor using tensor.array():

content.code_html:
const myArr = [[1, 2], [3, 4]];
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape);
tensorA.array().then(array => display(array[0]));

function display(data) {
  document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = data;
}

content.text: You can get the rank of a tensor using tensor.rank :
content.html: You can get the rank of a tensor using tensor.rank:

content.code_html:
const myArr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape);

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = tensorA.rank;

content.text: You can get the shape of a tensor using tensor.shape :
content.html: You can get the shape of a tensor using tensor.shape:

content.code_html:
const myArr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape);

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = tensorA.shape;

content.text: You can get the datatype of a tensor using tensor.dtype :
content.html: You can get the datatype of a tensor using tensor.dtype:

content.code_html:
const myArr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape);

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = tensorA.dtype;

content.text: Tensor Data Types
A Tensor can have the following data types:
content.html: A Tensor can have the following data types:

content.text: When you create a tensor, you can specify the data type as the third parameter:
content.html: When you create a tensor, you can specify the data type as the third parameter:

content.code_html:
const myArr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const shape = [2, 2];
const tensorA = tf.tensor(myArr, shape, "int32");
